PhD position at University of Geneva (UNIGE)

The Center for Advanced Modelling Science (CADMOS) has opened a PhD=20=20
position in high-performance computing (HPC) applied to natural=20=20
language processing at the University of Geneva, Switzerland. The=20=20
selected candidate is expected to work in collaboration with the =C9cole=20=
=20
Polytechnique F=E9d=E9rale de Lausanne (EPFL) and the UNDL Foundation in=20=
=20
designing and implementing efficient HPC methods for extracting and=20=20
processing multilingual resources for machine translation, information=20=20
retrieval and knowledge representation.

The ideal candidate should have a master degree in Computer Science=20=20
(or equivalent); familiarity with distributed and parallel computing;=20=20
good programming skills in Java; good knowledge of English (written=20=20
and spoken); interest in algorithms and statistical natural language=20=20
processing; and ability to meet deadlines and to work in a=20=20
collaborative environment. Proficiency in French will be a plus.

Candidates should send a CV and a motivation letter to phd@undlfoundation.o=
rg=20
  . The position is open now;  selection will start immediately and=20=20
continue until the position is filled.  The salary will be in=20=20
accordance with the rules of the University of Geneva for academic=20=20
personnel.

Contact person
Prof. Bastien Chopard
Computer Science Department
University of Geneva


--Boundary_(ID_B2MHzaNHbX1pzVNEIdZEsw)
